CODE OF CONDUCT

We are committed to creating a positive community and strive for exemplary behavior from all members, including:

- Communication in a welcoming and inclusive language
- Respect and empathy in all interactions
- Constructive criticism of others' work

We do not tolerate:

- Insults, personal attacks, or belligerent behavior
- Harassment and discriminatory behavior
- Politically or religiously polarized speech
- Any other behavior deemed inappropriate in a professional context

This code applies to all contributors in all spaces related to this project and to all individuals representing it.

Project moderators are responsible for maintaining harmony within the community and have the right to intervene in case of a conflict situation by rejecting or modifying a contributor's entire or partial contribution to the project and/or temporarily or permanently banning them. Any problematic behavior can be confidentially reported to the moderation team.